olive oil
1 onion
2 clove garlic
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 bunch parsley
1 packet hummus
1 tbs water (for the dressing)
1 packet beef mince
½ tbs white wine vinegar
1 sachet chermoula spice mix
1 packet tomato paste
1 tsp brown sugar
20 g butter
¼ cup water (for the beef)
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag salad leaves

Thinly slice the red onion. Finely chop the garlic. Finely chop the tomato and cucumber. Roughly chop the parsley leaves. In a small bowl, combine the hummus and water (for the dressing). Set aside.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. Add the onion and cook until softened, 3 minutes. Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the beef mince and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.

While the beef is browning, combine the cucumber, tomato and parsley in a medium bowl. Add the white wine vinegar and a generous drizzle of olive oil, then season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat and set aside.

Add the chermoula spice blend, tomato paste and brown sugar to the beef. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add the butter and water (for the beef) and simmer until the sauce has thickened, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

Heat the mini flour tortillas in a sandwich press or on a plate in the microwave for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

Bring everything to the table to serve. Build your tacos by topping the tortillas with mixed salad leaves, the Turkish-spiced beef and cucumber salsa. Dollop with the hummus dressing.